message.content:
cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a spiking neural network (SNN) and a learning algorithm based on Spike Timing Dependent Plasticity (STDP), which falls under the domain of neural computing. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper applies the proposed ReStoCNet and HB-STDP algorithm to the MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets for pattern recognition tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a learning algorithm for training the binary kernels forming ReStoCNet in an unsupervised manner, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture and learning algorithm for efficient neuromorphic computing, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the computational efficiency and memory footprint of the proposed ReStoCNet architecture, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
